rm{ISM}}$) models. The combined blue UV slopes and weak nebular\nemission are best-fit by models with significant ionizing photon escape from\nHII regions (f$_{\\rm{esc,HII}}$=0.5-0.8) and extremely low-metallicity massive\nstars (Z$_\\star$=0.01-0.06Z$_\\odot$). The discovery of these galaxies\nhighlights the potential for JWST to identify large numbers of candidate Lyman\nContinuum leaking galaxies in the reionization-era and suggests low-metallicity\nstellar populations may be common in dwarf galaxies at $z>7$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 2 Aug 2022 17:37:43 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 28 Nov 2022 21:48:59 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-12-28"}
