rvations accurately trace the cloud\nkinematics, except for the largest scales. The line-of-sight confusion\ncomplicates the interpretation of the kinematics, and limits the usefulness of\ncollapse indicators based on the blue asymmetry of optically thick lines. The\nngVLA will provide accurate data on the small-scale structure and the physical\nand chemical state of clouds, even in high-mass star-forming regions at\nkiloparsec distances. Complementary single-dish data are still essential for\nestimates of the total column density and the large-scale kinematics.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 3 Aug 2022 07:45:41 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-10-12"}
